yogasanas.name: Mountain pose
yogasanas.benefits: Improves posture, balance, and body awareness while promoting calm breathing.
steps: Stand upright with feet together and arms by your sides.
Distribute weight evenly across both feet.
Engage your legs and lengthen your spine.
Relax shoulders and breathe steadily.

yogasanas.name: Tree Pose
yogasanas.benefits: Enhances balance, concentration, and strengthens the legs.
steps: Stand straight and shift weight onto one leg.
Place the other foot on the inner calf or thigh.
Bring palms together at chest level.
Focus on a fixed point and breathe calmly.

yogasanas.name: Child Pose
yogasanas.benefits: Relieves stress, relaxes the back, and calms the mind.
steps: Kneel on the floor and sit back on your heels.
Lower your torso forward between your thighs.
Extend arms forward or rest them beside your body.
Breathe slowly and relax.

yogasanas.name: Warrior Pose I
yogasanas.benefits: Builds strength in legs and improves focus and stamina.
steps: Step one foot back and bend the front knee.
Square your hips forward.
Raise arms overhead with palms facing each other.
Hold steady and breathe.

yogasanas.name: Warrior Pose II
yogasanas.benefits: Strengthens legs, opens hips, and increases endurance.
steps: Spread legs wide and bend the front knee.
Extend arms parallel to the floor.
Turn head to gaze over the front hand.
Maintain steady breathing.

yogasanas.name: Warrior Pose III
yogasanas.benefits: Improves balance, coordination, and core strength.
steps: Shift weight onto one leg.
Extend the other leg straight back.
Lean torso forward and extend arms ahead.
Keep body in a straight line.

yogasanas.name: Cobra Pose
yogasanas.benefits: Strengthens the spine and opens the chest and lungs.
steps: Lie on your stomach with palms under shoulders.
Press lightly into hands and lift chest.
Keep elbows bent and shoulders relaxed.
Breathe comfortably.

yogasanas.name: Cat-Cow Pose
yogasanas.benefits: Improves spinal flexibility and relieves back tension.
steps: Start on hands and knees.
Inhale, arch your back and lift head.
Exhale, round your spine and tuck chin.
Flow slowly with breath.

yogasanas.name: Downward Facing Dog
yogasanas.benefits: Stretches the whole body and improves circulation.
steps: Start on hands and knees.
Lift hips upward forming an inverted V shape.
Press heels toward the floor.
Relax head and neck.

yogasanas.name: Bridge Pose
yogasanas.benefits: Strengthens the back and opens the chest.
steps: Lie on your back with knees bent.
Place feet hip-width apart.
Lift hips upward while pressing feet down.
Hold with steady breathing.

yogasanas.name: Seated Forward Bend
yogasanas.benefits: Stretches the spine and calms the nervous system.
steps: Sit with legs extended forward.
Inhale and lengthen spine.
Exhale and bend forward from hips.
Relax neck and shoulders.

yogasanas.name: Easy Pose
steps: Sit cross-legged on the floor.
Keep spine straight and shoulders relaxed.
Rest hands on knees.
Breathe naturally.

yogasanas.name: Corpse Pose
yogasanas.benefits: Promotes deep relaxation and mental clarity.
steps: Lie flat on your back.
Allow arms and legs to relax.
Close eyes and release tension.
Focus on slow breathing.

yogasanas.name: Legs Up the Wall
steps: Sit close to a wall.
Lie back and extend legs upward against wall.
Relax arms by your sides.
Breathe slowly.

yogasanas.name: Standing Forward Bend
steps: Stand tall with feet hip-width apart.
Bend forward from the hips.
Let head and arms hang down.
Breathe deeply.
